# Vertex GCP credits (portable)

Project **`codemonkeys-498819`** · region **`us-central1`**.

## What burns GCP credits (not Cursor billing)

| Tool | Command / path |
|------|----------------|
| Batch content jobs | `CodeMonkeys/scripts/vertex_burn.py --all` |
| CodeMonkeys agents | provider **`vertex-gemini`** or model **auto** |
| Verify this machine | `projects/shared/vertex-credits/verify_vertex.py` |

## One-time setup per machine

| OS | Run once |
|----|----------|
| Linux / macOS / WSL | `projects/shared/vertex-credits/setup.sh` |
| Windows | `powershell -File projects\shared\vertex-credits\setup.ps1` |

Config lives outside git:

- Linux: `~/.config/codemonkeys/vertex.env` (+ optional `vertex-sa.json`)
- Windows: `%APPDATA%\codemonkeys\vertex.env` (+ optional `vertex-sa.json`)

**Best cross-machine auth:** same service account JSON copied to both paths above (or password manager export). **Per-machine auth:** `gcloud auth application-default login`.

## Agent behavior

When building games, itch copy, payment flows, or franchise content at volume:

1. Prefer **`vertex_burn.py`** jobs over burning Cursor credits on repetitive generation.
2. Add new jobs to `CodeMonkeys/scripts/vertex_jobs.json` — output under `PixelSports/docs/vertex-generated/`.
3. Do **not** commit `vertex-sa.json`, `VERTEX_CREDENTIALS_JSON`, or `.env` secrets.

## Limits (honest)

- **Cursor chat/Agent** in the IDE still bills Cursor — Vertex hook is CodeMonkeys + burn script.
- Credits expire — check GCP Billing → Credits; set budget alerts.

